# WNBA Player Props PMF + Game Totals Model

A production-oriented WNBA port of the NBA player-props PMF framework:

- full discrete PMF per player/stat
- minutes × rate simulation for high-frequency counting stats
- sparse hurdle models for steals/blocks
- convolution for combo props
- role-aware PIT/isotonic calibration
- game-total PMF model
- market comparison against no-vig odds
- after-game scoring and calibration gates

## What is built

```text
src/wnba_props_model/
  data/          BDL REST client, ingestion, normalization
  features/      feature contract, rolling features, role buckets
  models/        quantile models, hurdle models, simulation, calibration, game totals
  evaluation/    NLL, RPS/CRPS, PIT, ECE, UCB95 market tests
  pipeline/      training, calibration, prediction, delivery
scripts/         command-line entrypoints
docs/            BDL API parity map and model contracts
tests/           math/contract tests
```

## Install

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
# optional if available
pip install -e ".[lgbm]"
cp .env.example .env
```

Set `BDL_API_KEY` in `.env` or your shell.

## Pull BDL WNBA history

```bash
python scripts/pull_bdl_history.py --start-season 2022 --end-season 2026 --out-dir data/raw/bdl
```

This writes:

- `data/raw/bdl/wnba_games.parquet`
- `data/raw/bdl/wnba_player_game_stats.parquet`

## Train player prop PMFs

```bash
python scripts/train_player_pmfs.py \
  --player-stats data/raw/bdl/wnba_player_game_stats.parquet \
  --games data/raw/bdl/wnba_games.parquet \
  --out-dir artifacts/models/player_props
```



## Build walk-forward OOF PMFs and calibrators

```bash
python scripts/build_oof_pmfs.py \
  --player-stats data/raw/bdl/wnba_player_game_stats.parquet \
  --games data/raw/bdl/wnba_games.parquet \
  --out-path data/processed/oof_pmfs.parquet \
  --min-training-days 365 \
  --window-days 28 \
  --draws 5000

python scripts/fit_calibrators.py \
  --oof-pmfs data/processed/oof_pmfs.parquet \
  --out-dir artifacts/models/calibration
```

OOF uses fewer draws by default for speed. Production delivery uses 50,000 draws.

## Train game totals

```bash
python scripts/build_game_totals.py \
  --games data/raw/bdl/wnba_games.parquet \
  --out-dir artifacts/models/game_totals
```

## Predict and deliver

```bash
python scripts/predict_today.py \
  --recent-player-stats data/raw/bdl/wnba_player_game_stats.parquet \
  --games data/raw/bdl/wnba_games.parquet \
  --raw-props data/raw/bdl/live/wnba_player_props_snapshot.parquet \
  --model-dir artifacts/models/player_props \
  --out-dir deliveries/$(date +%F)/wizard_of_odds
```

## Outputs

- `full_pmfs_wide.parquet`
- `fair_odds_board.parquet`
- `market_comparison.parquet`
- `publishable_edges.parquet`

## Important WNBA BDL parity issue

NBA BDL has lineups and box-score endpoints. The WNBA BDL docs checked for this build do not list matching `lineups` or `box_scores` endpoints. This repo handles that honestly:

- box-score training labels come from `wnba/v1/player_stats` and `wnba/v1/games`
- lineup context uses ex-ante fallback features from recent minutes, recent starts, and injuries
- `lineup_confirmed` is reserved for an external lineup source

See `docs/API_FEATURE_PARITY_MAP.md`.

## Calibration gates

| Gate | Threshold |
|---|---:|
| PIT KS | <= 0.075 |
| ECE | <= 0.025 |
| abs(mean error) | <= 0.15 |
| abs(variance error) | <= 0.20 |
| UCB95 log-loss delta | < -0.0025 |
| UCB95 Brier delta | < -0.0010 |
| Min rows for market superiority | 100 per stat×role |
| Production draws | 50,000 |

## Status

This is a buildable repository scaffold with the production contracts, feature map, PMF math, calibration math, delivery layer, and command-line pipeline in place. It still needs your actual BDL key/data and an OOF backfill run before any real performance or market-superiority claim can be made.
